Constructors - is a special method , it has same name as class name and it does not have any return type  and everytime you create an object it will call the constructor 

class Animal
{
    int age;
    String name;
    
    public Animal()
    {
        age = 7;
        name = "Ahad";
        System.out.println("name " +name+ " age" +age);
    }
    
    public static void main(String args[])
    {
        Animal a1 = new Animal();
        
    }
}


default and parametrised Constructors

class Animal
{
    int age;
    String name;
    
    public Animal()
    {
        age = 7;
        name = "Ahad";
        System.out.println("age " +age+ "name" +name);
    }
    
    
    public Animal(int age,String name)
    {
        this.age = age;
        this.name = name;
        System.out.println(age);
        System.out.println(name);
    }
    
    public static void main(String args[])
    {
        Animal a1 = new Animal(7,"Ahad");
        
    }
    
    
}
